multiplex quantitative real-time {PCRs.} The assay employs the interaction 
between gene-specific capture probes bound to thermostable microbeads and mobile 
gene-specific degradable detection probes which report the amplification. Our 
system requires only two encoding dyes for encoding of multiple microbead 
populations and one reporter dye for microbead bound capture probes for the 
discrimination of at least twelve amplification reactions. We used the method 
for the quantitative detection of several human and bacterial genes. The assay 
is amplicon size independent, requires no alteration of the {PCR} product, 
employs a simple probe structure and has no background fluorescence. Early 
results indicate that the amplification efficiency is similar to reactions in 
solution. 
